{"body": "This has been merged now so the discussion is moot, but as a point of principle (see comments on cd12c369961a612f6b083fc0e3b877cf59b737f4) you should have `.rvmrc` in your global `.gitignore` and then explicitly `git add -f` it in any projects where you want to share it, rather than madly adding it to the individual `.gitignore`s of every project where you don't want to share it.\r\n\r\nWhether omitting `.rvmrc` from Rails' `.gitignore` would communicate this point to anyone on the planet is, I suppose, a pretty academic consideration.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/793751", "created_at": "2011-02-21T16:45:08Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/194#issuecomment-793751", "updated_at": "2011-02-21T16:45:08Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 194, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/tomstuart", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/cd9b247e4507fed75312e9a42070125d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F766e428d1e232bbdd58664b41346196c.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/received_events", "gravatar_id": "cd9b247e4507fed75312e9a42070125d", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "tomstuart", "type": "User", "id": 3192, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomstuart/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52386607bd3543c15101278c"}, "id": 793751, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/194"}
